# API: ${ENDPOINT_NAME}

## Overview

Brief description of what this endpoint/API does.

## Endpoint

```
${METHOD} ${PATH}
```

## Authentication

| Type | Required | Header |
|------|----------|--------|
| Bearer Token | Yes | `Authorization: Bearer <token>` |

## Request

### Headers

| Header | Required | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| `Content-Type` | Yes | `application/json` |
| `X-Request-ID` | No | Idempotency key for retries |

### Path Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `id` | string | Yes | Resource identifier |

### Query Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `page` | integer | 1 | Page number |
| `limit` | integer | 20 | Items per page (max 100) |

### Request Body

```json
{
  "field1": "string — description (required)",
  "field2": 0,
  "nested": {
    "subfield": "string — description"
  }
}
```

## Response

### Success (200 OK)

```json
{
  "id": "res_abc123",
  "field1": "value",
  "created_at": "2026-01-15T10:30:00Z"
}
```

### Error Responses

| Status | Code | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| 400 | `INVALID_INPUT` | Request body validation failed |
| 401 | `UNAUTHORIZED` | Missing or invalid authentication |
| 403 | `FORBIDDEN` | Insufficient permissions |
| 404 | `NOT_FOUND` | Resource does not exist |
| 429 | `RATE_LIMITED` | Too many requests (retry after header) |

Error body format:
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "INVALID_INPUT",
    "message": "Human-readable error description",
    "details": [
      { "field": "field1", "issue": "must be non-empty" }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Examples

### cURL

```bash
curl -X ${METHOD} \
  https://api.example.com${PATH} \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "field1": "value"
  }'
```

### Python

```python
import httpx

response = httpx.${METHOD_LOWER}(
    "https://api.example.com${PATH}",
    headers={"Authorization": f"Bearer {token}"},
    json={"field1": "value"},
)
result = response.json()
```

### TypeScript

```typescript
const response = await fetch("https://api.example.com${PATH}", {
  method: "${METHOD}",
  headers: {
    "Authorization": `Bearer ${token}`,
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({ field1: "value" }),
});
const result = await response.json();
```

